## Full Feature Specification

### CRM Table (hero)
Columns: # | Company | Industry | City | Employees | Audit Score | Outdated Stack | Key Decision Maker | Status | Actions
- Audit Score = composite ((Modernity + Mobile + Function) / 3), color-coded chip
- Outdated Stack = Y/N badge (Y if any of: no HTTPS, legacy WP, no mobile, score < 4)
- Status dropdown (New/Contacted/In Progress/Ignored) — inline edit, persists via API
- Row checkbox for bulk selection
- Actions column: eye icon (drill-down), external link (website)

**Filters + Search (persistent in URL params):**
- Global text search (company name, city, DM name)
- Filter: Industry (multi-select), City/Region (Twin Cities / Greater MN / All), Audit Score range slider, Outdated Stack (Y/N/All), Status (multi-select)
- SMB filter toggle: show only 5-200 employees (default on, visible in toolbar)
- Sort: click any column header, asc/desc toggle

**Toolbar:**
- `+ Add Lead` (manual entry modal)
- `Run Discovery` (opens panel)
- `Bulk Edit Status` (enabled when rows selected)
- `Export CSV` (selected rows or all)
- KPI bar: Total leads | New | Contacted | In Progress | Avg Audit Score | Outdated Stack %

### Drill-Down Modal
Two-panel layout:
- **Left:** homepage screenshot (full-page img, scrollable); website URL; outdated stack flags listed (e.g., "Legacy WordPress detected", "Missing HTTPS", "Non-responsive layout")
- **Right:**
  - Company card: name, industry, city, employee range, website
  - Audit sub-scores: Modernity UI/UX (1-10 gauge), Mobile Responsiveness (1-10), Overall Functionality (1-10), Composite score
  - AI Audit Notes: 2-3 sentences per sub-score
  - Decision Maker card: name (partial last name gracefully handled — Apollo free tier masks last name), title, seniority tier (C-Suite / Director / Manager), enrichment source tag "Apollo", LinkedIn URL (if available), avatar placeholder with initials
  - Status editor + notes field (free text, persists)
  - Last-updated timestamp

### Discovery Panel (supporting 1)
Slide-in drawer from right.
- **Input fields:** Industry (multi-select, 6 categories), Region (Twin Cities / Greater MN / Both), Employee range (5-200 default), Keywords (optional)
- **Pipeline visualization:** 4 animated steps with live status dots:
  1. Search — Serper `/places` API query shown (`POST https://google.serper.dev/places`, JSON preview with `q`, `gl`, `hl`)
  2. Scrape — Playwright headless Chromium with flags (`--headless=new`, `--enable-unsafe-webgpu`, `--enable-features=Vulkan`), screenshot + HTML extraction shown
  3. WebGPU Audit — SmolVLM-256M-Instruct via `@huggingface/transformers` v3, token/score generation preview
  4. Enrich — Apollo.io People Search (`POST https://api.apollo.io/v1/people/search`), response field preview
- Each step shows realistic JSON snippet of what that stage produces
- On completion: appends 3-5 new randomized MN leads to the table
- Simulated 4-8 second animated sequence with real-looking progress

### WebGPU Audit Demo (supporting 2)
Dedicated tab/panel.
- **GPU Detection card:** `navigator.gpu` check → green/red badge; if available: `GPUAdapter` info (vendor, architecture, device type via `requestAdapterInfo()`)
- **Live Inference:** "Analyze a Website" input — enter any URL; fetches a screenshot (or uses a seeded placeholder); loads SmolVLM-256M-Instruct (`@huggingface/transformers` v3, `device: 'webgpu'`) in the browser; first-load shows progress bar with "Downloading model..." (15-25s); generates real sub-scores + rationale text
- **WASM fallback:** if `navigator.gpu` null, auto-falls back to `device: 'wasm'` (slower but functional); clearly labeled "CPU fallback — WebGPU not available"
- **Architecture explainer:** two tabs — (A) Browser path: Transformers.js WebGPU + SmolVLM-256M-Instruct + Playwright flags; (B) Python path: MLC LLM `mlc-llm` pip package + Metal/Vulkan backend
- **Package note visible in UI:** `@huggingface/transformers` v3 (renamed from `@xenova/transformers` v2)

---

## Resolved Research Decisions

| Question | Decision |
|----------|----------|
| WebGPU model | `HuggingFaceTB/SmolVLM-256M-Instruct` — 256M params, <1GB VRAM, 15-25s first load (cached), 80+ tok/s on M-series Mac |
| Package name | `@huggingface/transformers` v3 (npm install / CDN `https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@huggingface/transformers@3/dist/transformers.min.js`) |
| WebGPU inference location | CLIENT-SIDE in React dashboard (not in Playwright scraper). Flow: Python scrapes → Flask stores screenshot → React fetches screenshot → browser JS runs SmolVLM → POSTs scores back |
| Playwright flags | `--headless=new`, `--use-angle=vulkan`, `--enable-features=Vulkan`, `--disable-vulkan-surface`, `--enable-unsafe-webgpu`, `--disable-dev-shm-usage` |
| Enrichment API | Apollo.io only (Proxycurl shut down Jan 2025). People Search free tier, last name masked on free tier — DM card shows "Jane D." gracefully |
| Discovery API | Serper `/places` primary + Yelp Fusion (500 req/day free) supplemental |
| Flask blueprint DB | Own `clientfinder.db` (NOT mw.db) to avoid schema conflict; `PRAGMA journal_mode=WAL` |
| CORS | Inherited from `CORS(app)` in server.py — no per-blueprint config needed |

---

## Build Plan

### Stack
- **Vite 5 + React 18** (JSX, hooks, context) — complexity requires real component tree; `@huggingface/transformers` v3 is ESM-only (requires Vite build, cannot use CommonJS `<script>`)
- Build output: `../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/client-finder-1-0/`
- Source: `upwork-runs/client-finder-1-0/demo-src/`
- `vite.config.js`: `base: '/demos/client-finder-1-0/'`
- CSS: plain CSS custom properties (no Tailwind) with `tokens.css`

### File Structure (~14 files — justified at richness 10)
```
demo-src/
  index.html
  vite.config.js
  package.json
  src/
    main.jsx
    App.jsx
    styles/
      tokens.css          <- design tokens (all CSS vars)
      global.css          <- resets, layout, typography
    components/
      CRMTable.jsx        <- hero table (sort/filter/search/bulk/export)
      FilterBar.jsx       <- filter controls + KPI bar
      DrillDownModal.jsx  <- per-lead detail modal
      DiscoveryPanel.jsx  <- run discovery drawer + pipeline animation
      WebGPUPanel.jsx     <- WebGPU audit demo + architecture explainer
      StatusBadge.jsx     <- reusable status/score chips
    data/
      seedLeads.js        <- 50 MN leads (real cities, plausible names, Apollo partial names)
    hooks/
      useLeads.js         <- CRUD state + API calls (localStorage fallback if backend unavailable)
      useWebGPU.js        <- navigator.gpu detection + adapter info + SmolVLM loader
    utils/
      csvExport.js
      auditUtils.js       <- composite score calc, outdated-stack logic
```

### Backend (Flask blueprint — greenlit)
File: `../mw-backend/clientfinder_blueprint.py`
Prefix: `/clientfinder`
DB: `data/clientfinder.db` (own SQLite, separate from mw.db)

Endpoints:
- `GET /clientfinder/leads` — list all; supports `?industry=&status=&region=` filters
- `POST /clientfinder/leads` — add one or array of leads
- `PATCH /clientfinder/leads/<id>` — update status, notes, any field
- `DELETE /clientfinder/leads/<id>` — remove
- `GET /clientfinder/leads/export` — CSV download
- `GET /clientfinder/leads/stats` — KPI aggregates (counts by status/industry, avg score)

Schema: `id, company_name, industry, city, state, employee_count, website, screenshot_url, score_modernity, score_mobile, score_function, composite_score, outdated_stack, stack_flags, dm_name, dm_title, dm_seniority, dm_source, outreach_status, notes, created_at, updated_at`

Seeded: 50 MN leads on blueprint `init_db()` (idempotent — checks existing count).

Blueprint structure mirrors `spotify_blueprint.py`: `Blueprint("clientfinder", __name__, url_prefix="/clientfinder")`, own `_get_conn()`, no import from server.py, registered after existing blueprints.

---

## Seed Data Spec (50 leads)

Real MN cities:
- Twin Cities: Minneapolis, St. Paul, Bloomington, Edina, Eden Prairie, Plymouth, Minnetonka, Eagan, Roseville, St. Louis Park, Burnsville
- Greater MN: Duluth, Rochester, St. Cloud, Mankato, Moorhead, Winona, Brainerd, Fergus Falls

Industries (50 total):
- Entertainment (bowling, arcades, golf, events) — 7: e.g., Memory Lanes (Mpls), Pinstripes (Edina), Brunswick Zone (Brooklyn Park)
- Professional Services (ad agencies, law, accounting, architecture) — 10: e.g., North Loop Creative Agency, Summit Law Group; real examples: Periscope, Mono, Zeus Jones (Mpls)
- Home/Commercial Services (HVAC, plumbing, landscaping, cleaning) — 9: e.g., Genz-Ryan (Burnsville), Sedgwick Heating (Mpls), Northshore Landscaping
- Healthcare/Wellness (dental, PT, gyms, med-spas) — 9: e.g., Uptown Dental (Mpls), Summit Dental Partners, Lakeside PT
- Retail/Hospitality (restaurants, breweries, boutique retail, auto repair) — 8: e.g., Lake & City Brewing Co., Indeed Brewing, Fulton Beer, Surly Brewing (Twin Cities)
- Manufacturing/Logistics (machine shops, logistics, food producers) — 7: e.g., Great Northern Machining, Northland Logistics

Each lead:
- `employee_count`: random 5-200
- Plausible website URL (fabricated, e.g., `northloopagency.com`)
- Audit scores: varied (weighted low — more sales opportunity); modernity 2-8, mobile 2-9, function 2-8
- DM: first name + masked last initial (e.g., "Sarah C.") matching Apollo free-tier format; realistic title; seniority: C-Suite/Director/Manager
- Status mix: New x35, Contacted x8, In Progress x4, Ignored x3
- `stack_flags`: realistic subset of ["Legacy WordPress", "Missing HTTPS", "Non-responsive layout", "Outdated jQuery", "No meta viewport", "No SSL certificate"]
- `screenshot_url`: placeholder path (static image from public/demos/client-finder-1-0/assets/)

